  <div class="paragraph_wrapper" style="margin-top: 20px;">
    <p>
      <p>Nobody but Denzel Washington at his peak could have pulled this off. The unmistakable first bars of “Still D.R.E.” signal <i>Training Day</i>’s journey into a different L.A., one that looks like Dr. Dre and Snoop Dogg’s, and it sets up the dynamic between its two very different protagonists more powerfully than any lengthy dialogue could. But it’s also just really cool to have Denzel Washington say “you in the office, baby” and then hit the switches on his Chevrolet Monte Carlo before riding off into the city. — <i>ARR</i>
</p>
    </p>
